metadata.name: EYE IN THE LAKE
metadata.description:
This photo was taken with a drone in the Yarisli lake of BURDUR province, from a height of approximately 400 m.

The dryness of the summer months has reduced the water level in the lake, the birds and other creatures living in the lake are having a hard time.
Especially the habitats of migratory birds are disappearing day by day.

They walk for hours on the lake, which has started to dry, in the hope of finding food and feeding. The shapes they create during this time are interesting.

  I likened this image formed on the surface of the lake to the eye .

Maybe mother nature is trying to attract people's attention, trying to reveal the situation of drying lakes, birds and nature that are in danger of life.

Mother nature creates wonders with her art, it is pleasant to watch these images, but the truth is that nature disappears.

Place: AFYON / Turkey 

Date: 18.09.2022
